      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "# Version 1.0.0 is finally here, Huge Release!!! 💃🙌🎊\r\n\r\nI can't believe the last time I updated this plugin was almost **a year ago.** I have been a bit all over during that year. Regardless, I am currently out of work, so I have a lot of free time on my plate, So, I decided to try and finalize this plugin. I found people were still using it, and its the only thing I made that **people actually used**. This motivated me to polish it and make it better. Plus, I also don't like to keep things incomplete. This is probably the **final release**, I don't want to waste more time on this than I already have. Maybe in the future (another year from now?) I will make a new version if people are still using this and AI hasn't taken over our human souls. \r\n\r\n\r\nI am very excited to share this release, it has a lot of **new cool features** that I am really happy with, with some optimizations and enhancements.\r\n\r\nWithout further ado, Here is a list of the new stuff added (probably doesn't cover everything).\r\n- fixed color menu bug\r\n- added settings for default pin behavior\r\n- added setting for taskbar visibility\r\n- added button to toggle reading/writing mode\r\n- removed breadcrumb from sticky note titles to keep a minimal look\r\n- enhanced compatibility with macos\r\n- added setting to use the most recent used color\r\n- sticky notes can be stored and loaded when a workspace is closed (FINALLY!!!)\r\n- added command and setting for creating new sticky notes\r\n\r\nIf you find this plugin useful, please tell me. knowing that real people use the stuff I make, makes me happy ",
